- Configure Tauri Android project initialization and signing
- Build and publish APK artifacts to GitHub releases alongside desktop builds
- Consider adding APK signing with keystore for production releases

## DevDash

### In progress / next up

- `.env` / secrets manager: structured editor for `.env` files with masked values; optional sync to OS keyring
- Per-pane settings persistence (log filter, ports filter, git graph collapsed state survive restart) also enhance the UI by adding sort features to the panels with listings (Processes, Ports, Git). Additionally, integrating real syntax highlighting in the Editor and Systemd text view using CodeMirror 6 will improve readability and user experience. Notifications for long-running commands can be implemented using the Tauri notification plugin to keep users informed about the status of their tasks.

### Mid-tier features

- Docker compose support: list compose projects, up/down/restart per service, view logs
- Kubernetes panel: kubectl contexts, get pods, logs, exec into pods
- Cron editor: parse `crontab -l`, visual editor, save back
- Disk I/O + per-process network in Metrics (iostat / nethogs style)
- Consistent "open URL in browser" across all panels (logs, terminal, ports)

### Polish on existing panels (often higher ROI than new panels)

- Per-pane settings persistence (log filter, ports filter, git graph collapsed state survive restart)
- Real syntax highlighting in the Editor + Systemd text view (CodeMirror 6) — replaces the regex-based highlighter and the plain textarea
- Multi-select on Processes panel: kill multiple, sort by column
- Notifications when long-running commands finish (Tauri notification plugin)

### Small utility panels (low-effort, low daily use — defer)

- Markdown preview pane
- JSON / YAML formatter scratchpad
- Regex tester
- Color picker / palette inspector
- Hex / base64 converter
- JWT decoder
- UUID / ULID generator
- Cron expression visualizer
